roam /rəʊm/

(roaming,roamed,roams) 

1. V-T/V-I If you roam an area or roam around it, you wander or travel around it without having a particular purpose. 闲逛; 漫游 

例： Barefoot children roamed the streets. 光着脚的孩子们在街上闲逛。 

例： I spent a couple of years roaming around the countryside. 我花了几年时间在乡村漫游。

